message: Read the full article. Foreign Policy article presents the results of the presidential primaries and places the Historical Pact (Pacto Historico) between the left and the center-left: Colombia's 2022 Presidential Primary Results. Left to center-left (Pacto Histórico) Center-left to center (Centro Esperanza): Center-right to right (Equipo por Colombia)
Page of Foreign Policy: Historic Pact is left-wing to center-left
Wikipedia does not prohibit the use of references that are in other languages. Besides this is a foreign article. It would be discriminatory and illogical.
Added referenced information and removed unreferenced or incorrectly referenced information.
Source: section ''Ballot Access'' of this page

The rule you cite says: Citations to non-English reliable sources are allowed on the English Wikipedia. There is no rule in Wikipedia that prohibits using media or articles that are in other languages ​​as references. In addition, this is an article of foreign origin. And the sources are reliable and from important and recognized media.
All references are reliable, are from important and recognized media. There is no reason why they are invalid.
None Wikipedia rules prohibit the use of media from other languages ​​as references, especially if it is an article whose origin is from a country where another language is spoken.
The reference nowhere says ''21st century socialism''. Absolutely nowhere.
References and the main Colombian media define the coalition as center-left and left-wing. Also as a progressive and environmentalist.
Stop deleting information with valid sources. What you do is unjustified.
